{{Expand Korean|1=음력 3월 10일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}}
{{Lunisolar March|qq=}} 
'''March 10''' is the 10th day of month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March (Yayoi)|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} . It's {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  day is {{ill|Shakkō|ja|赤口|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} . 


== Events ==

* {{ill|Emperor Monmu|ja|文武天皇|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  4 ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  {{ill|700|ja|700th year|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  {{ill|April 3|ja|4月3日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – Buddhist monk {{ill|Dōshō|ja|道昭|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  is cremated, marking the first recorded cremation in Japan.

* {{ill|Wadō (era)|ja|和銅|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  3 (Julian {{ill|710|ja|710th year|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  {{ill|April 13|ja|4月13日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – {{ill|Empress Genmei|ja|Emperor Genmei|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  relocates the capital from {{ill|Fujiwara-kyō|ja|藤原京|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  to {{ill|Heijō-kyō|ja|Heijō-kyō|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} .

* {{ill|Jōgan (Japan)|ja|貞観|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  8 (Intercalary March) (Julian {{ill|866|ja|866th year|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  {{ill|April 28|ja|4月28日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – {{ill|Ōtenmon Incident|ja|応天門の変|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} : The {{ill|Ōtenmon Gate|ja|応天門|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  is set ablaze. {{ill|Ban no Yoshio|ja|伴善男|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} , a descendant of the {{ill|Ōtomo clan|ja|大伴氏|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} , is exiled as the arsonist, marking the decline of the clan’s political influence.

* {{ill|Eiwa (Japan)|ja|永和|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  4 / {{ill|Tenju (Japan)|ja|天授 (日本)|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  4 (Julian {{ill|1378|ja|1378th year|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  {{ill|April 7|ja|4月7日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – {{ill|Ashikaga Yoshimitsu|ja|足利義満|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  moves the {{ill|Muromachi shogunate|ja|Ashikaga Shogunate|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  to the newly constructed {{ill|Muromachi Palace|ja|室町殿|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  (Hana no Gosho) in Kyoto.

* {{ill|Daoguang Emperor|ja|道光|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  19 ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  {{ill|1839|ja|1839th year|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  {{ill|April 23|ja|4月23日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – Qing officials arrive in {{ill|Guangdong|ja|広東|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  to enforce a crackdown on {{ill|opium|ja|阿片|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} , leading to large-scale confiscation and destruction.

* {{ill|Meiji (era)|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  2 (Gregorian {{ill|1869|ja|1869th year|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  {{ill|April 21|ja|4月21日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – The {{ill|Tokyo City|ja|東京市|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  abolishes the {{ill|machinushi|ja|町名主|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  system, dismissing 238 town chiefs.

* Meiji 5 (Gregorian {{ill|1872|ja|1872nd year|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  {{ill|April 17|ja|4月17日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – The {{ill|Ministry of Education (Japan)|ja|文部省|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  establishes a museum department (now the {{ill|Tokyo National Museum|ja|東京国立博物館|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} ) and hosts the first {{ill|exposition|ja|博覧会|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  at {{ill|Yushima Seidō|ja|湯島聖堂|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} 's Taiseiden ({{ill|Yushima Seidō Exposition|ja|湯島聖堂博覧会|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} ).

== Births ==

* {{ill|Chōshō (era)|ja|長承|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  3 (Julian {{ill|1134|ja|1134th year|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  {{ill|April 6|ja|4月6日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – {{ill|Yasuda Yoshisada|ja|安田義定|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} , Japanese {{ill|samurai|ja|武将|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  (+ {{ill|1194|ja|1194th year|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} ).

